properties.headline: Flood Advisory issued February 5 at 10:24AM CST until February 6 at 10:15PM CST by NWS Omaha/Valley NE
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Omaha has issued a

* Flood Advisory for...
An Ice Jam in...
North central Dodge County in east central Nebraska...

* Until 1015 PM CST Thursday.

* At 1015 AM CST, emergency management reported an least one, but
perhaps two separate ice jams from County Road F near Scribner and
upstream to near the Dodge-Cuming line. Minor floding was reported
on County Road C. While flooding is not eminent for Highway 275,
further rises could result in officials closing the road. This new
advisory will replace the previously issued advisory.

* Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Rural Scribner, Powder Horn State Wildlife Management Area, Dead
Timber State Recreation Area, and County Road C.
properties.instruction:
A Flood Advisory means river or stream flows are elevated, or ponding
of water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent.
